@attribute [Route("/components/" + nameof(HxTabPanel))]
@attribute [Route("/components/" + nameof(HxTab))]

<ApiDoc Type="typeof(HxTabPanel)">
	<DocHeading Title="Basic usage" />
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxTabPanel_Demo_BasicUsage)" Tabs="false" />
	<DocAlert Type="DocAlertType.Info">
		Wrapping <code>HxTab</code> components with <code>&lt;AuthorizeView&gt;</code> or similar structures is not supported.
		<code>HxTabPanel</code> expects <code>HxTab</code> components to be its direct children.
		To dynamically control tab visibility, set the <code>HxTab.Visible</code> parameter
		or use conditional rendering with an <code>@@if</code> condition.<br />
	</DocAlert>

	<DocHeading Title="Getting/setting active tab from code" Id="active-tab" />
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxTabPanel_Demo_ActiveTabId)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Nav variants" />
	<p>You can choose any variant of <code>nav</code> using the <code>@nameof(HxTabPanel.NavVariant)</code> parameter.</p>
	<DocHeading Title="Tabs" Level="3" />
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxTabPanel_Demo_NavVariantTabs)" />
	<DocHeading Title="Pills" Level="3" />
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxTabPanel_Demo_NavVariantPills)" />
	<DocHeading Title="Standard" Level="3" />
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxTabPanel_Demo_NavVariantStandard)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Vertical orientation" Id="vertical" />
	<p>
		Set <code>Orientation="<a href="/types/NavOrientation#Vertical">NavOrientation.Vertical</a>"</code> to stack the tab
		navigation next to the tab content. Combine it with <code>@nameof(HxTabPanel.NavVariant).@nameof(NavVariant.Pills)</code> for vertical pills.
		Vertical orientation applies to the <code><a href="/types/TabPanelVariant#Standard">TabPanelVariant.Standard</a></code> variant.
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxTabPanel_Demo_NavVariantPillsVertical)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Button-based tabs" Id="buttons" />
	<p>
		Set <code>TabHeadersAsButtons="true"</code> to render the tab headers as <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> elements instead of anchors.
		Buttons are the recommended markup for tabs that only switch content without navigating to a URL.
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxTabPanel_Demo_ButtonTabs)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Fade effect" Id="fade" />
	<p>
		Set <code>Fade="true"</code> to make the tab panes fade in when activated.
		The fade transition requires the default <code>RenderMode="<a href="/types/TabPanelRenderMode#AllTabs">TabPanelRenderMode.AllTabs</a>"</code>.
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxTabPanel_Demo_Fade)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Card with tabs" />
	<p>When <code>Variant</code> is set to <code><a href="/types/TabPanelVariant#Card">TabPanelVariant.Card</a></code>, the tab navigation is placed in the card header and tab contents go into the card body.</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxTabPanel_Demo_CardMode)" />

	<DocHeading Id="render-mode" Title="Rendering only active tab contents" />
	<p>
		By default, the <code>HxTabPanel</code> renders the contents of all tabs, and the visibility of the active tab is controlled by CSS.
		If you want to render the active tab only, you can use the <code>RenderMode="TabPanelRenderMode.ActiveTabOnly"</code> parameter.
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxTabPanel_Demo_RenderMode)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Accessibility" Id="accessibility" />
	<p>
		<code>HxTabPanel</code> renders the WAI-ARIA tabs pattern out of the box:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>the navigation is a <code>role="tablist"</code> (with <code>aria-orientation="vertical"</code> when <code>Orientation</code> is vertical),</li>
		<li>each tab header is a <code>role="tab"</code> with <code>aria-selected</code>, <code>aria-controls</code> and a roving <code>tabindex</code> (<code>0</code> for the active tab, <code>-1</code> for the others),</li>
		<li>each tab pane is a <code>role="tabpanel"</code> linked back to its header via <code>aria-labelledby</code>.</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		For tabs that switch content without navigating, prefer <code>TabHeadersAsButtons="true"</code> so the headers are
		focusable <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> elements activated with <kbd>Enter</kbd>/<kbd>Space</kbd>.
	</p></ApiDoc>

<ApiDoc Type="typeof(HxTab)" />
